#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.94"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.94:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.94:0.2"
msgid "10. Asuravagga "
msgstr "10. Demons "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.94:0.3"
msgid "94. Tatiyasamādhisutta "
msgstr "94. Immersion (3rd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.94, sc1
msgctxt "an4.94:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.94:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.94:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, na lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya. "
msgstr "One person has internal serenity of heart, but not the higher wisdom of discernment of principles. "

msgctxt "an4.94:1.4"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa. "
msgstr "One person has the higher wisdom of discernment of principles, but not internal serenity of heart. "

msgctxt "an4.94:1.5"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo na ceva lābhī hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na ca lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya. "
msgstr "One person has neither internal serenity of heart, nor the higher wisdom of discernment of principles. "

msgctxt "an4.94:1.6"
msgid "Idha pana, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya. "
msgstr "One person has both internal serenity of heart, and the higher wisdom of discernment of principles. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.94:2.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "As for the person who has serenity but not discernment: they should approach someone who has discernment and ask: "

msgctxt "an4.94:2.2"
msgid "‘kathaṃ nu kho, āvuso, saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā? "
msgstr "‘Reverend, how should conditions be seen? "

msgctxt "an4.94:2.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā? "
msgstr "How should they be comprehended? "

#. VAR: vipassitabbā → passitabbā (mr)
msgctxt "an4.94:2.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti? "
msgstr "How should they be discerned?’ "

msgctxt "an4.94:2.5"
msgid "Tassa so yathādiṭṭhaṃ yathāviditaṃ byākaroti: "
msgstr "That person would answer from their own experience: "

msgctxt "an4.94:2.6"
msgid "‘evaṃ kho, āvuso, saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is how conditions should be seen, comprehended, and discerned.’ "

msgctxt "an4.94:2.7"
msgid "So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya. "
msgstr "After some time they have both serenity and discernment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.94:3.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya na lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "As for the person who has discernment but not serenity: they should approach someone who has serenity and ask: "

msgctxt "an4.94:3.2"
msgid "‘kathaṃ nu kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ? "
msgstr "‘Reverend, how should the mind be stilled? "

#. VAR: sannisādetabbaṃ → sanniyādetabbaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "an4.94:3.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ? "
msgstr "How should it be settled? "

#. VAR: cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ → ekodikattabbaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.94:3.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ? "
msgstr "How should it be unified? "

msgctxt "an4.94:3.5"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabban’ti? "
msgstr "How should it be immersed in samādhi?’ "

msgctxt "an4.94:3.6"
msgid "Tassa so yathādiṭṭhaṃ yathāviditaṃ byākaroti: "
msgstr "That person would answer from their own experience: "

msgctxt "an4.94:3.7"
msgid "‘evaṃ kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabban’ti. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, this is how the mind should be stilled, settled, unified, and immersed in samādhi.’ "

msgctxt "an4.94:3.8"
msgid "So aparena samaye lābhī ceva hoti adhipaññādhammavipassanāya lābhī ca ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa. "
msgstr "After some time they have both discernment and serenity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.95, sc4
msgctxt "an4.94:4.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo na ceva lābhī ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa na ca lābhī adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ceva ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya so upasaṅkamitvā evamassa vacanīyo: "
msgstr "As for the person who has neither serenity nor discernment: they should approach someone who has serenity and discernment and ask: "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.2"
msgid "‘kathaṃ nu kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ? "
msgstr "‘Reverend, how should the mind be stilled? "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ? "
msgstr "How should it be settled? "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.4"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ? "
msgstr "How should it be unified? "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.5"
msgid "Kathaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabbaṃ? "
msgstr "How should it be immersed in samādhi?’ "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.6"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā? "
msgstr "How should conditions be seen? "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.7"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā? "
msgstr "How should they be comprehended? "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.8"
msgid "Kathaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti? "
msgstr "How should they be discerned?’ "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.9"
msgid "Tassa so yathādiṭṭhaṃ yathāviditaṃ byākaroti: "
msgstr "That person would answer as they’ve seen and known: "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.10"
msgid "‘evaṃ kho, āvuso, cittaṃ saṇṭhapetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ sannisādetabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ ekodi kātabbaṃ, evaṃ cittaṃ samādahātabbaṃ, evaṃ saṅkhārā daṭṭhabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā sammasitabbā, evaṃ saṅkhārā vipassitabbā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, this is how the mind should be stilled, settled, unified, and immersed in samādhi. And this is how conditions should be seen, comprehended, and discerned.’ "

msgctxt "an4.94:4.11"
msgid "So aparena samayena lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya. "
msgstr "After some time they have both serenity and discernment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.94:5.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yvāyaṃ puggalo lābhī ceva hoti ajjhattaṃ cetosamathassa lābhī ca adhipaññādhammavipassanāya, tena, bhikkhave, puggalena tesu ceva kusalesu dhammesu patiṭṭhāya uttari āsavānaṃ khayāya yogo karaṇīyo. "
msgstr "As for the person who has both serenity and discernment: grounded on those skillful qualities, they should practice meditation further to end the defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.94:5.2"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four people found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.94:5.3"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
